$MS earned only 11.5% on equity in 1Q2019 Memo to Gorman: A bank/invt co that is earning this amt on its equity should only be priced at book value. Here is the history of $MS ROE. @SaraEisen @Sarge986 @tomkeene @jimcramer macrotrends.net/stocks/chart…

Bingo! ROEs for banking sector have been crushed since 2007 (Gorman crickets on this impt metric). If you earn 10%-13% ROE a bank stock should basically trade at book. If you earn 30%+ should trade at a multiple of 2.5-3x book value.

Just one more thing.. @realmoney People Get Ready "People, get ready There's a train a-coming You don't need no ticket You just get on board" - The Impressions (written by Curtis Mayfield), People Get Ready piped.video/watch?v=VOXmaSCt… If the market was a song it would obviously

be The Impressions, People Get Ready. (I favor The Chambers Brothers' version of the song piped.video/watch?v=y0FnjkSF…. But Rod Stewart and Jeff Beck's version was really good too piped.video/watch?v=T43m6dcM…) Named by Rolling Stones Magazine as the 24th greatest song of all-time,

this 1965 song was a terrific bundle of contradictions. A gospel arrangement in a quartet style that was even then archaic, right down to its bluesey guitar figure, married to a lush string setting that would sound excessive ten years later. What lets the record work is the

sweetness, soulfulness and endearing innocence of the singing. The lyrics rank with " A Change is Gonna Come," as an expression of the interlinked concerns of the civil rights movement, the black church and the R&B record industry. And even "A Change is Gonna Come" didn't

expropriate the imagery of black spirituals with quite such slick precision. So, people get ready for the results of the US/China trade negotiations. My "impression" is that it will leave us with a sour note realmoney.thestreet.com/doug… on Monday morning. Bottom Line
